{
  "texts": [
    "By fitting different GMMs with varying L values using the EM algorithm, BIC can be used to measure the performance of each and assess their modeling capabilities, ultimately useful in estimating the number of signals given the observed data.Figure 6 explains the process that is followed by the GMM clustering method in order to detect and localize the signal and spoofing signals.",
    "In particular, a running example where three signals (i.e.",
    "one legitimate and two spoofers) are present in the dataset.",
    "Initially, the proposed method uses the computed CAF delay/Doppler map, shown in Fig. 6a, to feed a DNN classifier.",
    "The DNN model is in charge of producing probability ratio maps, used to determine the presence or absence of signals in the map."
  ]
}